      "writtenOn": "2020-10-16T16:31:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Speed is basically a straight 2x improvement. We do the chop logic once now instead of twice, and we don\u0027t do a divide in between anymore either. Precision is also better since we don\u0027t divide then re-chop on the chopped points.\n\nChopping at inflections is a sizable chunk of the work it takes to prepare strokes for indirect draws, so this helps a lot on strokes where both inflections are inside 0..1.\n\nGold says it sees pixel differences, but then when I click it doesn\u0027t show me any. It\u0027s certainly possible there will be pixel differences (improvements) though that need to be rebaselined. What bots can I run to check?",
      "parentUuid": "abad5160_77cd62a5",
      "revId": "45be2cbd64655d3e5e9e8e060d78c6e9dd220970",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
